This is not a certificate issue.

Root cause is here:

Unable to tunnel through proxy. Proxy returns "HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden"

Your app reached the proxy, but the proxy refused CONNECT to:

https://ws.idms.lexisnexisrisk.com

So production proxy/firewall allowlist is missing the new production domain.

The later errors:

RdpDeviceAssessmentResponse block missing
Request Id cannot be found for Person Id

are downstream symptoms because the LexisNexis/RDP call never completed.

What to do now:

1. Ask network/security to allowlist:

ws.idms.lexisnexisrisk.com:443
*.lexisnexisrisk.com:443

2. Confirm old prod URL is still allowed:

ws.idms.lexisnexis.com:443

3. From prod app server, test:

curl -v -x <proxy-host>:<proxy-port> https://ws.idms.lexisnexisrisk.com/restws/identity/v3/accounts/27223/workflows/usps.change.address.wf/conversations

4. If proxy returns 200, 401, 403 from LexisNexis, or any app-level response, connectivity is working.
5. If it still says:

Unable to tunnel through proxy
Proxy returns 403

then network/proxy rule is still blocking it.

Bottom line: certs are not the blocker. The new LexisNexisRisk production domain is blocked by USPS proxy/firewall.
